---
import LegalDocument from '../../../components/LegalDocument.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { appLegalProfiles } from '../../../data/appLegalProfiles';
import type { AppLegalProfile } from '../../../data/appLegalProfiles';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return appLegalProfiles.map((profile) => ({
    params: { slug: profile.slug },
    props: { profile },
  }));
}

interface Props {
  profile: AppLegalProfile;
}

const { profile } = Astro.props;
const eulaUrl = `/apps/${profile.slug}/eula/`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${profile.name} Privacy Policy`}
  description={`Privacy Policy for ${profile.name}.`}
>
  <LegalDocument
    overline={profile.name}
    title="Privacy Policy"
    description={`This Privacy Policy explains how ${profile.legalProvider} collects, uses, shares, retains, and protects information for ${profile.name}.`}
    effectiveDate={profile.effectiveDate}
  >
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy applies to {profile.name} (the "App"), {profile.appDescription} It also applies to related support and public pages that link to this policy. The <a href={eulaUrl}>End User License Agreement</a> governs use of the App.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you use the App on behalf of a company or other organization, that organization controls the data connected to the App and decides which reports are generated and which end users or recipients may receive them. In that case, we process information as directed by the organization and as needed to provide the App.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>Depending on how the App is configured and used, we may collect or access the following categories of information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account and contact information:</strong> name, business name, email address, role, support contact details, and related account information.</li>
      <li><strong>Authorization and connection information:</strong> QuickBooks Online company identifiers, realm IDs, OAuth tokens, connection status, scopes approved by the user, and other information needed to maintain authorized connections. We do not ask for or store QuickBooks passwords.</li>
      <li><strong>QuickBooks Online data:</strong> {profile.quickBooksDataDescription}</li>
      <li><strong>Report content and recipient details:</strong> generated reports, report parameters, delivery history, and recipient names or email addresses when needed to deliver reports authorized by the customer.</li>
      <li><strong>App usage and diagnostics:</strong> log data, feature activity, browser or device information, IP address, timestamps, errors, and security events.</li>
      <li><strong>Support communications:</strong> information you provide when you contact us, including messages, screenshots, attachments, and issue history.</li>
      <li><strong>Website analytics:</strong> basic analytics about visits to public pages that link to this policy, such as page views and browser information.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>
      We use information to {profile.dataPurpose} We only use QuickBooks Online data for the stated purpose of the App and related support, security, compliance, and maintenance activities.
    </p>
    <p>More specifically, we may use information to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>connect to QuickBooks Online and retrieve data authorized by the user;</li>
      <li>generate, display, synchronize, maintain, and deliver authorized reports;</li>
      <li>authenticate users, manage accounts, and administer permissions;</li>
      <li>provide support, troubleshoot problems, and communicate service updates;</li>
      <li>monitor reliability, prevent fraud, investigate misuse, and secure the App;</li>
      <li>improve App functionality and user experience; and</li>
      <li>meet legal, contractual, accounting, audit, and compliance obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Share Information</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell QuickBooks Online data or personal information. We do not share QuickBooks Online data with third parties for advertising. We may share information only in the following limited ways:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> vendors that help us host, operate, secure, analyze, support, or maintain the App, subject to appropriate confidentiality or data protection obligations.</li>
      <li><strong>Intuit and connected services:</strong> information sent to or received from QuickBooks Online and other services that you authorize.</li>
      <li><strong>Your organization and authorized users:</strong> information may be available to administrators, internal users, and report recipients authorized by your organization.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal and safety reasons:</strong> when required by law, legal process, or government request, or when reasonably necessary to protect rights, safety, security, or prevent misuse.</li>
      <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> as part of a merger, acquisition, financing, reorganization, or sale of assets, subject to this policy or a policy with materially similar protections.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      We retain information for as long as needed to provide the App, support the customer relationship, comply with legal and accounting obligations, resolve disputes, enforce agreements, maintain backups, and protect security.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you disconnect the App from QuickBooks Online, the App will stop retrieving new QuickBooks Online data through that connection. You may request deletion of App data by contacting us. We will delete or de-identify information within a commercially reasonable period unless we must retain it for legal, security, backup, audit, or legitimate business reasons. Backup copies may persist for a limited period before routine deletion.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards designed to protect information against unauthorized access, loss, misuse, alteration, and disclosure. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
    <p>
      You can control the QuickBooks Online scopes and companies you authorize through Intuit's authorization flow and account settings. You can also request access, correction, deletion, or export of personal information by contacting us. We may need to verify your identity or authority before completing a request.
    </p>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live, you may have additional privacy rights under applicable law. These may include the right to know what personal information is collected, request deletion or correction, receive a portable copy, opt out of certain sharing or targeted advertising, and appeal a rights decision. We do not sell personal information.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Aggregated or De-Identified Information</h2>
    <p>
      We may use aggregated or de-identified information to understand usage, improve reliability, and develop App functionality. We will not attempt to re-identify de-identified information except as permitted by law, such as to test whether de-identification measures work.
    </p>

    <h2>8. International Processing</h2>
    <p>
      We are based in the United States, and information may be processed in the United States or other locations where we or our service providers operate. If you access the App from outside the United States, you understand that information may be transferred to and processed in countries with different data protection laws.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The App is intended for business use and is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to this Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the effective date above and provide notice when required. Continued use of the App after an update means the updated policy applies.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or privacy requests can be sent to <a href={`mailto:${profile.contactEmail}`}>{profile.contactEmail}</a>. {profile.legalProvider} is based in {profile.location}.
    </p>
  </LegalDocument>
</BaseLayout>
